 If a form script is loaded using an XHR from a web server, it is executed using eval(). To debug it, you need to use browser-specific debugger extensions.
Debugging Form Scripts in Google Chrome If you are using the Google Chrome debugger, you can add the debugger; directive to the source code of the script:
&lt;form role=&quot;form&quot;&gt; &lt;script cam-script type=&quot;text/form-script&quot;&gt; debugger; &lt;/script&gt; &lt;/form&gt;

